<hl>
<seg id=1> Huang Sihua: Malaysia will create better circumstances next year to keep 10 billion in foreign capital in the stock market. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Kuala Lumpur Malaysian Vice Minister of Finance Huang Sihua said that next 1 September when the supervision measures of foreign capital were carried out for a year, it's supposed that more than 10billion ringgit of foreign capital would leave the stock market. Therefore, the government would create better investment conditions through various measures to encourage foreign capital to stay in Malaysia. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> He said that according to the rate of economic development of the third quarter, the Malaysian economy was recovering. It's believed that next September, the economy would be stable, and the market would be active, and foreign businessmen would decide to invest in Malaysia. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Huang Sihua made a speech the day before yesterday at the Economic Report and Communication Conference of the Malaysian Chinese Business Association. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> He emphasized that the Malaysian government would decide the rate of exchange to be 1 Dollar to 3.8ringgit. This would encourage investors to make long-term plans, and make up their minds to invest without worrying about currency fluctuation again. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> He said that the supervision measures would carry on for a period of time until the international currency market became stable. An international system of supervision would be set up, and currency exchange would become transparent to prevent the financial storm attacking Southeast Asia. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> On the other hand, Huang Sihua said that through the adjustment of the Ministry of Finance, the Ministry of Finance had approved 20% of the loan applications, which could not be approved. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> He said that the Ministry of Finance would provide consultation and support for those companies that hadn't been approved, and let the companies carry out their plan smoothly to push market activities forward. </seg>
</p>
